= Vert.x Apex

The link:groovydoc/io/vertx/groovy/ext/apex/core/Router.html[`router`] is really cool stuff, here is an example

[source,{lang}]
----
import io.vertx.groovy.ext.apex.core.Router
def router = Router.router(vertx);
def subRouter = Router.router(vertx);
router.mountSubRouter("/subpath", subRouter);
subRouter.route("/foo").handler({ rc ->
  rc.response().setStatusMessage(rc.request().path()).end();
});

----